cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with salient object detection using Convolutional Neural Networks. Additionally, it involves transfer learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with both RGB and depth modalities. Finally, the use of pre-training and optimization techniques suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
